parameters:
\n<Chief Guard>Are you Rain, the holy knight? Thank you for
coming all this way.
\n<Chief Guard>I am Caldo, the chief guard. Nice to meet you.
\OC[31]\N<Rain>I'm Rain. Nice to meet you too.

\n<Caldo>I've been hearing rumors for a while now. They say
you're called \ANN[1] and are feared by the demons
for your fighting prowess.

\CE[78]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>\....\....\.Oh? I've just been fighting
enemies non-stop, so I don't really
pay attention to rumors.

\CE[78]\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(I don't know who started it... but... I wish they
would stop using that name, it's embarrassing...)

\n<Caldo>It must have been far from the capital to here. We
have prepared a place for you to relax, would you
like to take a break for now?

\CE[78]\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, please don't worry about it. Instead, please
tell me about the abnormality in this town right
away.

\n<Caldo>I believe you have heard, but compared to a year
ago, there is clearly a deterioration in public
safety in this town.

\n<Caldo>There has been an increase in adventurers and
bounty hunters due to the increase in monsters,
but there are also rumors of suspicious movements
by thieves.
\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Thieves, huh? So, the rumors are true then?
\CE[79]\n<Caldo>Yes... It's a shameful story, but that's correct.

\n<Caldo>Originally, this town's soldiers were not
numerous, so the response has been delayed.
Various information is still in confusion and
hasn't been thoroughly examined yet.

\n<Caldo>In other words, it's an embarrassing story... but
I can't tell you more than what I've already
informed you in advance.

\CE[79]\n<Caldo>However, I believe that the people from the Holy
Demon Church who noticed this abnormality early on
might be able to provide more detailed
information.

\n<Caldo>The ones who discovered the new dungeon were also
members of the church.

\n<Caldo>The church is located \c[17]here and to the north.
It may be a bit of a journey, but could you go
there and speak with the priest?

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Understood. Thank you for your help even though
you're busy.

\n<Caldo>I apologize for not being able to guide you.
Please take care of me.
'Go to the Holy Demon Church and listen to what the priest has to say'

\n<Caldo>The church is located to the north of \c[17]town.
It may be a bit of a journey, but please take care
of me.

\n<Caldo>I'm sorry, I also want to use my legs, but there
are too many documents to check... I apologize for
making the Holy Knight-sama run around!

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Please don't worry about that. Let's each fulfill
our necessary roles.

\n<Caldo>Thank you for your hard work. I will also proceed
with the investigation as much as possible on my
end, so...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Kaldo-san, when I had that fragment investigated,
it was confirmed that there is still a high
possibility of the device existing.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>It's possible that one of them might be located in
the northwest, but is there any suspicious place
around that area?

\n<Caldo>Beyond the \C[17]Hakusei Forest\C[0], there is a
cave infested with monsters. It's not particularly
large, and there aren't any strong monsters
inside, but it should be sealed off, so there
shouldn't be any human traffic.

\n<Caldo>However, it might be the perfect place for demons
to move secretly...!

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Certainly suspicious. I will head there right
away!

\n<Caldo>I understand... However, I've also heard that area
is territory for thieves. Are you okay going
alone?

\n<Caldo>Yes, recently there seems to be a group of thieves
calling themselves the 'Yamimozuku' operating near
Hakudeti. Although their activities haven't been
too conspicuous yet, it's been bothering me a
little.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Compared to demons, thieves shouldn't be a
problem. Besides, time is of the essence.

\n<Caldo>I see... Understood. I will inform Meryl and Phils
about this. There are also traps in the northeast
dungeon, so please be careful!

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Yes, thank you for your concern. I'll be going
now.
'Lets investigate the cave beyond the Forest of Hakusei'

\n<Caldo>That captured thief still hasn't said anything.
I'll make them talk even if I have to use force.

\n<Caldo>The cave is located \C[17] beyond the Hakusei
Forest. Please be careful as there are traps in
the northeast dungeon \C[0].

\n<Caldo>Ah, is this the adventurer training facility to
the northeast from here? It's true that anyone can
use it, basically.

\n<Caldo>However, lately there have been a lot of rough
individuals, so please be careful.

\n<Caldo>Is it a dungeon located on the southeast coast? It
certainly has become a tourist attraction now. And
since it's near the beach, there are also many
people who come for swimming.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... If there's a device in such a place, it
could have a significant impact on the people
nearby. We need to head for an investigation right
away...

\n<Caldo>I apologize for being insensitive, but if
there were no devices in the vicinity, Rain-san,
wouldn't it be nice for you to take a little rest?

\n<Caldo>Well, um... objectively speaking, I think you
might be working too hard... How about taking a
little break...

\n<Caldo>I'm sorry, it was none of my business! A mere
soldier like me shouldn't have said
anything.........

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, you were concerned about me. Thank you very
much.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Indeed, I may have been acting a bit too hastily.
I appreciate your concern.

\n<Caldo>Even though the guards are trained, they're
desperately trying to withstand 'Nightmare
Heaven'... so please show some restraint...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Meryl-san, I heard that you informed everyone
about the situation. Thank you for your help.

\CE[94]\OC[25]\N<Meryl>N-No... I'm just glad that you're safe, Rain-
san...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>...? Is something the matter? You don't seem like
yourself, Meryl-san.

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[25]\N<Meryl>Um, well... since there are people from the church
too... I was wondering if it's okay for me, being
a witch and all, to be here...

\n<Frist>Don't worry. Our Holy Magic Church doesn't teach
any hostility towards witches.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>And besides, Meryl-san informed us about something
important that concerns the peace of this town. We
can't do anything that would exclude someone like
that.

\n<Caldo>I've heard about your achievements from Rain-san.
I'm truly grateful.
\CE[94]\OC[25]\N<Meryl>If that's the case, then I'm glad... hehehe.

\CE[79]\n<Frist>As expected, we have to strike at the root cause
after all...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>But, Rain-san, it's reckless to infiltrate the
enemy's hideout alone!

\CE[94]\n<Caldo>However, since they specifically requested us, it
will be difficult for us to infiltrate...

\n<Frist>Moreover, from what I've heard, this Demon person
seems to be quite cunning. There's no doubt that a
trap has been set.
\n<Caldo>What do you think about it, \.\. Rain- san?

\CE[78]\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>To be honest, I don't know. I can't say that I'm
in perfect condition either, and I don't know the
extent of Demon's abilities...

\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I have no choice but to go alone. There is no
other way to defeat Demon and save Hakudeti...!

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[25]\N<Meryl>Um, do you have the fragments of the fourth
device?

\CE[94]\OC[25]\N<Meryl>If we analyze the four fragments, we might be able
to discover something that can counter 'Nightmare
Heaven'! I will proceed with that investigation!

\OC[25]\N<Meryl>If there's no other choice but to do it, then we
have to try doing what we can! In order to lighten
Rain-san's burden even just a little, I'll do
everything that I can!

\n<Caldo>Indeed, as Meryl-san said. If there is only one
path, then we have no choice but to give it our
all and move forward...!

\n<Caldo>We, the guards, will secure the route to Mount
Goryou and thoroughly interrogate the captured
'Dark Owls' to extract information!

\n<Frist>Let's make sure we can support Rain-san. I'm sure
Saint-sama will also cooperate.
\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Phils>Yes! I will do everything I can right now...!

\CE[79]\n<Frist>We'll leave the timing of departure to Rain-san.
Until then, let's each do our best with what we
can do now.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I understand....\.With this... let's truly...
end it!

\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(I also need to prepare myself as best as
possible.
\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(Today, I'll contact Jazz and... rest my body.)
'Contact Jazz regularly and take care of your body'

\EMP Gigigigi... someone else's documents are in
my possession...

\EMPAh~ The documents just keep piling up... It's
so frustrating...

\EMP Hey, miss, save that kind of play for
private. You've got a sexy body, after all.

\EMP Damn it, because of the increase in monsters,
I can't keep up with the maintenance of my
equipment.

\EMP Whoa!! I-I feel energized!! I want to have
sex!!

\EMP Sigh... I really want to meet my partner...
It's been three days of non-stop work...

\EMP Another pervert... What's happening to this
town...!

\EMP Hey, hey! Stop that while I'm cooking! But
wait, later I want to take a good look at you in
that outfit!!

\EMP Since everyone seems busy, I'll make sure to
treat you all to a delicious meal!
